ratings.en: Ye Shall Not Eat of It, Neither Shall Ye Touch It, Lest Ye Die
Appoint a Teacher for Yourself and Avoid Doubt
Traineth My Hands for War, and My Fingers for Battle
If He Come to Slay Thee, Forestall by Slaying Him
Who Is Powerful? One Who Overcomes His Inclinations
And Esau Said to Jacob: Pour Into Me Some of This Red, Red, for I Am Faint
God of Great Deeds, Find Us Forgiveness, at the Time of Ne'ila
He Perceives a Matter's Outcome at Its Inception
